🔹 locate (Fast File Search)
locate is used to quickly find files by name. It uses a pre-built database (updated using updatedb).

🛠️ Syntax:

        locate [options] pattern

📌 Common Options:

        -i → Case-insensitive search

        -c → Count number of matches

        -r → Use regular expressions

🧪 Examples:

        locate myfile.txt                   # Find all paths containing 'myfile.txt'
        locate -i readme                    # Case-insensitive search
        locate -c ".png"                    # Count all .png files